FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776066987
OL,3,CIrish police break up oil refinery
OL,4,Cprotest as country rocked by fuel
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,FTrucks and tractors continued to block
OL,8,Faccess to vital fuel depots and a
OL,9,Fmajor port, and vehicles clogging
OL,10,Ftraffic led to closures of part of the
OL,11,Fmain highway around Dublin as well as
OL,12,Fsections of other major roadways.
OL,14,FIrish police Commissioner Justin Kelly
OL,15,Fsaid enforcement would be ramped up
OL,16,Fbecause protesters were illegally
OL,17,Fblockading critical infrastructure and
OL,18,Fendangering public safety because of
OL,19,Fthe impact gas shortages could have on
OL,20,Femergency response from paramedics and
OL,21,Ffirefighters.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776066987
OL,3,CIrish police break up oil refinery
OL,4,Cprotest as country rocked by fuel
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,F"These are blockades. They are not a
OL,8,Flegitimate form of protest," Kelly
OL,9,Fsaid. "We gave the blockaders fair
OL,10,Fwarning that we were moving to
OL,11,Fenforcement and they choose to ignore
OL,12,Fit and continue to hold the country to
OL,13,Fransom."
OL,15,FIreland has been rocked by the
OL,16,Fconflict in the Middle East, causing a
OL,17,Fspike in fuel costs with many petrol
OL,18,Fstrations running out of fuel
OL,19,Faltogether.
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@\O]qD@GOUuD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776066987
OL,3,CIrish police break up oil refinery
OL,4,Cprotest as country rocked by fuel
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,FMore than a third of the 1,500 service
OL,8,Fstations had run out of fuel on
OL,9,FSaturday and that number was expected
OL,10,Fto grow dramatically if the roadblocks
OL,11,Fremain, Fuels for Ireland chief
OL,12,Fexecutive Kevin McPartlan said.
OL,14,FGovernment officials and a negotiator
OL,15,Fsaid progress was made on talks
OL,16,FSaturday to resolve the dispute.
OL,18,FGer Hyland, president of the Irish
OL,19,FRoad Haulage Association, who is
OL,20,Facting on behalf of some protesters,
OL,21,Fsaid he empathises with their plight.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776066987
OL,3,CIrish police break up oil refinery
OL,4,Cprotest as country rocked by fuel
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,F"They're hard-working business people,
OL,8,Fand they're just trying to survive and
OL,9,Fkeep their business afloat, the same
OL,10,Fas any of the rest of us here at these
OL,11,Fnegotiations," he said.
OL,13,FThe protests began on Tuesday and have
OL,14,Fgrown as word spread on social media,
OL,15,Fleading truckers, farmers, and taxi
OL,16,Fand bus operators to stage blockades
OL,17,Fand call for caps on fuel prices or
OL,18,Ftax cuts.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776066987
OL,3,CIrish police break up oil refinery
OL,4,Cprotest as country rocked by fuel
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,FGovernment officials, who had already
OL,8,Fintroduced measures to ease the burden
OL,9,Fof price rises, have been baffled over
OL,10,Fthe rationale behind the protests
OL,11,Fbecause the global price spike is due
OL,12,Fto the conflict in the Middle East
OL,13,Fthat has restricted oil exports.
OL,15,FPlumber Paddy Murray said he joined
OL,16,Fthe protest outside the port in
OL,17,FRosslare because he'd paid taxes all
OL,18,Fhis life and was looking for the
OL,19,Fgovernment to help him with the cost
OL,20,Fof living.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776066987
OL,3,CIrish police break up oil refinery
OL,4,Cprotest as country rocked by fuel
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,F"We can't continue to do business with
OL,8,Fthe cost of fuel, cost of wages,
OL,9,Feverything," Murray told national
OL,10,Fbroadcaster RTE.
OL,12,F"We need somebody to help. It's the
OL,13,Fgovernment's here like, to, represent
OL,14,Fus. You know, do your job. We're the
OL,15,Fworking lads that keep everything
OL,16,Fgoing. We're the working lads that pay
OL,17,Ftaxes."
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
