OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776066987
OL,3,CIrish police break up oil refinery
OL,4,Cprotest as country rocked by fuel
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,8,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,9,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,10,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,12,FTwo weeks ago, the government approved
OL,13,Fa range of measures to cut fuel
OL,14,Fprices, including a temporary
OL,15,Freduction in excise taxes on motor
OL,16,Ffuels, expansion of a rebate for
OL,17,Ftruckers and bus operators that use
OL,18,Fdiesel fuel, and extension of a
OL,19,Fprogram that helps low-income people
OL,20,Fwith their heating costs.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776066987
OL,3,CIrish police break up oil refinery
OL,4,Cprotest as country rocked by fuel
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,FBut those reductions were quickly
OL,8,Fovertaken as international prices
OL,9,Fcontinued to rise.
OL,11,FProtests began with slow-moving
OL,12,Fconvoys that restricted access to some
OL,13,Fof the busiest streets in Dublin and
OL,14,Fblocked fuel depots that supply half
OL,15,Fthe country.
OL,17,FSome protesters slept in their
OL,18,Fvehicles overnight, demanding that
OL,19,Fgovernment representatives speak with
OL,20,Fthem.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31811
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776066987
OL,3,CIrish police break up oil refinery
OL,4,Cprotest as country rocked by fuel
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,FPrime Minister Micheal Martin said on
OL,8,FFriday that the country was on the
OL,9,Fbrink of turning tankers away at ports
OL,10,Fduring a global shortage and was in
OL,11,Fjeopardy of losing its oil supply.
OL,13,F"It is unconscionable, it's illogical,
OL,14,Fit is difficult to comprehend," Martin
OL,15,Ftold national broadcaster RTE.
OL,17,FPolice in Northern Ireland said they
OL,18,Fwere monitoring social media posts
OL,19,Fcalling for similar action.
